'''Reporting''' is a tool used to flag inappropriate behavior and content to the VRChat Trust & Safety team. Conduct is based off of VRChat's [[Special:MyLanguage/Community Guidelines|Community Guidelines]], and [[Special:MyLanguage/Terms of Service|Terms of Service]].  In addition, you can also {{VRC link|https://feedback.vrchat.com/bug-reports|report bugs}} and {{VRC link|https://help.vrchat.com/hc/en-us/requests/new |security exploits}} to VRChat.

== Overview ==

Reporting is a very important process to ensure the safety and experience of all users, while blocking only locally curates the experience for yourself. The report process is anonymous, and users will be unable to tell whether or not something has been reported by you. Likewise, to protect user privacy, [[Special:MyLanguage/Bans|results of moderation action]] will not be disclosed to the reporter.

You can learn more about the various methods and alternatives for reporting in the [[Special:MyLanguage/Trust and Safety|Trust and Safety]] article, such as hiding avatars, muting a user, Safe Mode, and the Go Home button.

== Effective reporting ==

Reporting in-app is the most streamlined method to flag content and behavior. If necessary, to offer more conclusive data in a moderation report, VRChat's development team may recommend [https://help.vrchat.com/hc/en-us/requests/new submitting a moderation report] on the [[Special:MyLanguage/Resources|Help website]] at ''help.vrchat.com.'' See more about [[Special:MyLanguage/Reporting#Reporting on the VRChat website|reporting on the VRChat website]].

In an effective report, users are able to:

* Browse additional helpful resources, via the Help website
* Describe the situation more effectively
** Including or specifying offending users or content
* Attach media, such as:
** Photographic evidence
** Recorded video evidence
** Log files

